quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  6,74,"And (remember) when Ibrahim said to his father, Azar: "Do you (really) take idols as gods? I am afraid you and your people are in open error.""
  6,75,"And thus We showed Ibrahim the kingdom of the heavens and the earth, so that he may be firm in belief."
  6,76,"So, when the night enveloped him, he saw a star. He said, "This is my Lord." But, when it vanished, he said, "I do not like those who vanish.""
  6,77,"Later, when he saw the moon rising, he said, "This is my Lord." But, when it vanished, he said, "If my Lord does not guide me, I shall be among those gone astray.""
  6,78,"Thereafter, when he saw the sun rising, he said, "This is my Lord. This is greater." Again, when it vanished, he said, "0 my people, I am free of whatever you associate with Allah."
  6,79,"I have, indeed, turned my face straight towards the One who created the heavens and the earth, and I am not one of those who associate partners with Allah.""
  6,80,"And his people argued with him. He said, "Do you are with me about Allah while He has already led me to the right path, and I do not fear what you associate with Him unless, of course, something is willed by my Lord? My Lord encompasses everything with His knowledge. Would you, then, take no lesson?"
  6,81,"And how can I fear what you associate with Him, while you do not fear that you have associated with Allah some-thing for which He has sent down no authority to you? Now, which of the two parties has more right to be in peace? (Tell me) if you know.""